Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.
50603d67-d5f5-459b-b9db-9599adc0d9ae.272ea71d-a5a2-4d72-8580-199fe48c128a.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

50603d67-d5f5-459b-b9db-9599adc0d9ae.4559ff8c-ca3f-46d3-90a0-ff5d13d6a2ce.description=This will sort a table based upon one column in the table. If all of the entries in that column are numeric the sort will be numeric, otherwise it will be alphabetic. 
Inputs\:
Table\: the table to sort
columnDelimiter - the character used to delimit columns
rowDelimiter - the character used to delimit rows
column - the number of the column to sort on(starting at 1).
reverse - set to "true" to make the sort a reverse sort

Results\:
The sorted table output with the same row and column delimiters

Responses\:
success - if the sort completed
failure - if there was an error, for example the specified column was missing in one or more entries
50603d67-d5f5-459b-b9db-9599adc0d9ae.476b9ef4-f323-4ae0-9191-68ebe82f56f0.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

50603d67-d5f5-459b-b9db-9599adc0d9ae.4f436815-c700-4166-993c-c276bbb26b22.description=
Synopsis

    This flow generates a volume name based on the vServer name. The volume name is generated in numeric order.
    generateVolumeName performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve a list of volumes based on the vServer name using the HPOO flow getVolumes.
      2. If no volumes exist, set the new volume name as VOL01 (denoting the first volume in a series).
      3. If volumes exist, sort the list of volume names in alphanumeric order.
      4. Look at the first volume on the list and determine if the net index is greater than or less than nine.
      5. Pass the volume name back to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer to be used in the flow (required).
    siteId - The ID number of the site where the product is located.
    datacenter - The datacenter in which to create the customer's vServer.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow;  {what does this flow return and how is it returned?}  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.

50603d67-d5f5-459b-b9db-9599adc0d9ae.b6796b64-0277-41bb-bad5-73863a542f67.description=
Synopsis

    This flow generates a volume name based on the vServer name. The volume name is generated in numeric order.
    generateVolumeName performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve a list of volumes based on the vServer name using the HPOO flow getVolumes.
      2. If no volumes exist, set the new volume name as VOL01 (denoting the first volume in a series).
      3. If volumes exist, sort the list of volume names in alphanumeric order.
      4. Look at the first volume on the list and determine if the net index is greater than or less than nine.
      5. Pass the volume name back to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer to be used in the flow (required).
    siteId - The ID number of the site where the product is located.
    datacenter - The datacenter in which to create the customer's vServer.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow;  {what does this flow return and how is it returned?}  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.

Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

50603d67-d5f5-459b-b9db-9599adc0d9ae.d5ef2258-782e-45ab-b198-44ebfbd4f43a.description=
Synopsis

    This flow retrieves information about aggregates.
    getAggrs performs the following steps\:
      1. Pass the flow inputs in and assign the optional argument variables for the configuration.
      2. Call the remote action server (RAS) perl with the inputs.
      3. Validate the XML document from the RAS results.
      4. Query the XML document for the results. If the code is invalid, encode the invalid XML and set the reason for failure based on the reason code (\= or not \= to 0).
      5. If the code is valid, query the results for a status. If the status is not passed, provide a reason for the error.
      6. Pass the information to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    aggregateName - The NetApp aggregate name where the vServer's root volume is created.
    homeId - The aggregate's disks are assigned to this node ID.
    homeNode - The aggregate's disks are assigned to this node name.
    ownerId - The aggregate is assigned ownership of this node ID. Normally, homeId matches ownerId, but may be changed by SFO takeover to match the takeover node and                                   restored by SFO giveback to match the homeId. CFO takeover and giveback do not affect the ownerId.
    ownerName -  The aggregate is assigned ownership of this node name. Normally, homeName matches ownerName, but may be changed by SFO takeover to match the takeover                                   node and restored by SFO giveback to match the homeName. CFO takeover and giveback do not affect the ownerName.
    node - A list of node names. If the aggregate name is also specified the matching aggregate on given nodes is returned. If it isn't specified, all the aggregates on a specified node                   are returned. If this element is omitted when the request is sent, all matching aggregates in the cluster are returned.
      Valid Values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default Values\: None.
    
    isHybrid - If true, the aggregate currently contains both solid state drive (SSD) and non-SSD redundant array of inexpensive disks (RAID) groups.
    isHybridEnabled - If true, the aggregate is eligible to contain both SDD and non-SSD RAID groups.
      Valid Values\: True, False
      Default Value\: 
    
    isInconsistent - Determines whether the aggregate is inconsistent.
      Valid Values\: True, False
      Default Value\: False

    optArgVars- The optional argument variables for the configuration (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system-defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case aggregate information.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Optional inputs restrict the search, if none are given, all aggregates in the cluster are returned.
